file=Product/spec/operational/commands/spec-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "write prd", "spec this", "amend the prd", "out of scope" \| prd-discipline \| /prd \| · tb=\| "backlog", "prioritize", "rice", "groom", "age out", "next sprint view" \| backlog-rules \| /backlog \| · tb=\| "is this worth doing", "size this", "do-nothing cost", "should we build" \| opportunity-assessment \| /assess \| · tb=\| "acceptance criteria", "hand to eng", "testable", "criteria dispute", "bounced criterion" \| acceptance-criteria-handoff \| /criteria \| · p:Precedence=1. New ideas start at opportunity-assessment — /prd on an unassessed idea bounces to /assess.\n2. Release-time disputes → acceptance-criteria-handoff (frozen text arbitrates), whatever else is running.\n3. Ranking questions inside a PRD flow stay in backlog-rules; the PRD only cites its rank.\n